    <div class="container">

        <section id="dangers">
            <h2>Dangers of Joining Gangs</h2>
            <p>Gangs may seem like a place to belong, but they bring serious risks. Members often face violence, arrest, and lifelong criminal records. Many also become trapped in cycles of fear, poverty, and mistrust.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Risk of injury or death from violence</li>
                <li>Permanent criminal record affecting jobs and travel</li>
                <li>Involvement in illegal activities</li>
                <li>Loss of trust and safety in the community</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="prevention">
            <h2>How to Prevent Youth Violence</h2>
            <p>Communities can protect young people by giving them safe spaces, strong support networks, and positive activities to join. Education, mentorship, and strong family bonds are key.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Encourage after-school programs</li>
                <li>Promote open communication with trusted adults</li>
                <li>Get involved in sports, arts, and skill-building clubs</li>
                <li>Stay away from unsafe areas and negative influences</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="organizations">
            <h2>Organizations That Help</h2>
            <p>These groups work to keep youth safe and guide them toward a better future:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://www.end-violence.org/" target="_blank">Global Partnership to End Violence Against Children</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.unicef.org/protection/violence-against-children" target="_blank">UNICEF – Violence Prevention</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.youth.gov/" target="_blank">Youth.gov – Gang Prevention</a></li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <a href="youth_violence_info.pdf" class="download-btn" download>Download PDF</a>

